        "summary":  "AWS introduced the Claude Apps Gateway, a self-hosted control plane for centrally managing Claude Code and Claude Desktop deployments across enterprise development teams. The gateway integrates with OIDC-compliant identity providers via SSO, enforces policies by IdP group, sets spending limits per user/group/organization, and routes telemetry to CloudWatch, Prometheus, or third-party platforms. Traffic can be directed through Amazon Bedrock or Claude Platform on AWS with cross-region failover support.",
