        "summary":  "Sam Altman has proposed giving the U.S. government a 5% stake in OpenAI ΓÇö worth roughly $320 per American household based on the company\u0027s $852B valuation ΓÇö drawing on Alaska\u0027s oil dividend model to frame AI wealth distribution as a public benefit. The proposal currently functions more as a compelling narrative than a concrete policy, with Senator Bernie Sanders proposing a more aggressive 50% stake alternative. The real strategic value for OpenAI is improved public perception and favorable regulatory positioning during a period of intense government scrutiny.",
