        "theme":  "Models",
        "summary":  "Research documented in a paper titled Artificial Hivemind shows substantial output homogeneity across 25 major LLMs ΓÇö models consistently produce the same metaphors, the same random numbers, and the same brand suggestions regardless of prompt variation. Australian startup Springboards built Flint, trained on Alibaba\u0027s open-source Qwen 3, to identify decision points where more diversity is possible and introduce structured variation. Marketing professionals report practical value for brainstorming, though experts caution that over-reliance on any AI tool reduces original human thinking.",
